snippet.textDisplay:
Linus! you could make a video about the actual real problem with the budget relation between the price of a good PC and the price of a competent monitor for it. Because as I had to experience while building mine, I've seen that actually by buying a 1000$ PC requires to buy a 400$ monitor just to run without making any bottleneck. Yes, I'm talking about decent VA/IPS panels at 1440p at 144/240Hz. 
Maybe a video showing the real cost of a full setup (or at least the components that could make a bottleneck like pc and monitor). And find the sweet spot for either 1080p at 144/240Hz, 1440p at 144/240Hz and well... 4K at 60Hz?
That video could help everyone a LOT to choose between a real good 1080p experience and a 1440p experience without messing up by getting a beast PC and a sh*tty monitor.

And then maybe you could send it to me if you thought this was a good idea ;3

Hope you could read this comment at least, I like all your videos, explanations and "expensive-drops".
